on:<\/strong>\u00a0Analyze existing processes (marketing campaigns, sales motions, revenue ops, hiring, employee on\/offboarding) and design\/document improvements for efficiency.<\/li>\n<li><strong>CRM Administration &amp; Reporting:<\/strong>\u00a0Maintain HubSpot CRM hygiene; build dashboards, triggers and automated alerts; generate weekly\/monthly\/quarterly executive reports.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Cross-Functional Collaboration:<\/strong>\u00a0Serve as liaison between Marketing, Sales Ops, R&amp;D and Product: lead syncs, resolve issues, align on objectives and deliverables.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Vendor &amp; Contract Management:<\/strong>\u00a0Source, negotiate and manage vendors (e.g., Drata for compliance, event vendors, website developers); coordinate contracts with Legal.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Sales &amp; Marketing Operations:<\/strong>\u00a0Oversee SalesOps tooling (HubSpot flows, RB2B, Swan), website content\/UX updates, print &amp; swag fulfillment, and social-media design and coordination.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Finance &amp; Compliance Coordination:<\/strong>\u00a0Partner with Finance and Legal on budgets, forecasting, expense tracking, and SOC 2\/compliance workflows.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Talent Acquisition &amp; Hiring:<\/strong>\u00a0Define job requirements, draft and post job ads, coordinate candidate pipelines, schedule and conduct interviews, and manage offer processes.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Presentation &amp; Event Support:<\/strong>\u00a0Develop slide deck skeletons for board meetings and executive reviews; collect inputs and coordinate updates from stakeholders; support planning and execution of company events.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Office &amp; Administrative Management:<\/strong>\u00a0Manage expenses, vendor relationships, office logistics, and CEO\/CPO assistance (calendar, meeting follow-ups, ad hoc support).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Required Qualifications &amp; Skills<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience or a degree in business management.<\/li>\n<li>3+ years in operations, program management, or revenue operations within a tech or AI startup environment.<\/li>\n<li>Eagerness to take on a multifaceted role with potential for growth.<\/li>\n<li>Fluent in English, both written and spoken.<\/li>\n<li>Analytical mindset with a track record of using data to drive decisions and improve processes.<\/li>\n<li>Proactive problem-solver comfortable in a fast-paced, ambiguous environment.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Nice to have<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong project management skills; proficient with Notion<\/li>\n<li>Proficiency in CRM administration (e.g., Salesforce, HubSpot), Notion and and reporting tools (Google Sheets).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Ideal Candidate<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your career development is really important to you, and want a role that will evolve as you do, in a company that is building in the most innovative tech area: AI Agents.<\/li>\n<li>You bring successful professional experience in any of these areas: HR, sales, business development, support, or administrative roles.<\/li>\n<li>Tech-savvy and an AI enthusiast.<\/li>\n<li>Problem-solver with a proactive approach.<\/li>\n<li>Organized and detail-oriented.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>What We Offer<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>A chance to be part of a startup&#8217;s growth story from early on.<\/li>\n<li>A dynamic role with the opportunity to shape your career path.<\/li>\n<li>Competitive compensation and the potential for professional development.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Note: This role is for an individual contributor business operations manager at an early stage startup.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Overview xpander.ai\u00a0is an\u00a0open-source, multi-framework platform for building and managing AI Agents. Our platform handles the full software development lifecycle for enterprise teams that are building AI Agents, including agent state and memory, tool calling, visual workbench, agent to agent handoffs, MCP, agent triggering